        "byline": "By <a href=\"https://www.columbiaspectator.com/contributors/Elizabeth-Commisso/\">Elizabeth Commisso</a>\nEdited by <a href=\"https://www.columbiaspectator.com/contributors/Jessica-Li/\">Jessica Li</a>",
        "methodology": "Starting on Aug. 18, Spectator Graphics batch-sent the pre-semester survey to all emails scraped from the Columbia University Directory. This included email addresses of students from Columbia College, the School of General Studies, and the School of Engineering and Applied Science in the classes of 2022, 2023, and 2024. We also shared the survey through class group chats on GroupMe and class Facebook pages, and especially within Barnard and class of 2025 chats. On Aug. 22, we gained access to the emails of the class of 2025 and forwarded the survey to their inboxes. Within 24 hours, 415 out of 451 responses were first years. We stopped accepting responses on Aug. 23 at 11:59 p.m. EST.",
